### Test Auto-Incrementing Problem Numbers

### 1. First, login to get a token
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "test",
  "password": "test"
}

### 2. Create a test problem (should get problem number 26)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/problems/test-create
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 3. Create another test problem (should get problem number 27)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/problems/test-create
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Create a third test problem (should get problem number 28)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/problems/test-create
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Get all problems to see the sequential numbering
GET http://localhost:5000/api/problems
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Create a problem manually with specific data
POST http://localhost:5000/api/problems
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Manual Test Problem",
  "description": "This problem was created manually",
  "difficulty": "Medium",
  "category": "API & Backend",
  "tags": ["Manual", "Test"],
  "acceptanceRate": 75,
  "likes": 10
}
